The paper deals with the problem of finding pure Nash equilibria in polymatrix games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The games are defined on weighted directed graphs, which suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DS). The authors also mention the use of algorithms and complexity theory to study the problem, which points to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves analyzing tractable cases and proving NP or coNP-completeness, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
